Step 1: User Input (Text)
   - User provides input text.

Step 2: Flask App (app.py)
   - Flask app processes user input.

Step 3: Trainer Module (trainer/trainer.py)
   - Processes input data (gram.json and intents.json).

Step 4: Gram Module (trainer/gram.py)
   - Handles the training process.

Step 5: Output Model (data/output/attention.model)
   - Trained model is saved.

Step 6: HTML Template (templates/index.html)
   - Displays output to the user.

Step 7: CSS Styles (static/css/style.css)
   - Styles for HTML presentation.

Step 8: User/Bot Images (static/images/)
   - Images used in the user interface.

Step 9: Output Model (data/output/attention.model)
   - Trained model is used for responding to user input.

Step 10: End
   - Interaction cycle completes.
